* '''{{lang|uk|Людмила}}''' ''([[Ludmila (given name)|Lyudmyla]]'' {{IPA-uk|lʲudˈmɪlɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Ludmila (given name)|Ludmila]], of [[Slavic name|Slavic origin]]. * '''{{lang|uk|Майя}}''' ''(Mayya'' {{IPA-uk|ˈmɑjjɑ|}}). * '''{{lang|uk|Маргарита}}''' ''(Marharyta'' {{IPA-uk|mɑrɦɑˈrɪtɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Margaret]] and [[Marjorie]], of Persian origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Марина}}''' ''([[Maryna (disambiguation)|Maryna]]'' {{IPA-uk|mɑˈrɪnɑ|}}), from [[Marina (given name)|Marina]], of Latin origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Марія}}''' ''([[Mariya]]'' {{IPA-uk|mɑˈrʲijɑ|}}), from [[Maria (given name)|Maria]], equivalent to [[Marie (given name)|Marie]], [[Mary (name)|Mary]] and [[Miriam (given name)|Miriam]], of Hebrew origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Марфа}}''' ''([[Marfa (disambiguation)|Marfa]]'' {{IPA-uk|ˈmɑrfɑ|}}), '''{{lang|uk|Марта}}''' ''([[Marta (given name)|Marta]]'' {{IPA-uk|ˈmɑrtɑ|}}), from [[Martha (given name)|Martha]], of Judeo-Aramaic origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Меланія}}''' ''([[Melania|Melaniya]]'' {{IPA-uk|mɛˈlɑnʲijɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Melanie]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Мирослава}}''' ''(Myroslava'' {{IPA-uk|mɪrɔˈslɑwɑ|}}), feminine of ''Myroslav.'' * '''{{lang|uk|Михайлина}}''' ''(Mykhaylyna'' {{IPA-uk|mɪxɑjˈlɪnɑ|}}), feminine of ''Mykhaylo,'' equivalent to [[Michelle (name)|Michelle]], of Hebrew origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Надія}}''' ''([[Nadia|Nadiya]]'' {{IPA-uk|nɑˈdʲijɑ|}}), meaning "hope," calque from Greek {{lang|grc|Ἐλπίς}} ''([[Elpis]]).'' * '''{{lang|uk|Наталія}}''' ''([[Nataliya]]'' {{IPA-uk|nɑˈtɑlʲijɑ|}}), '''{{lang|uk|Наталя}}''' ''([[Natalya]]'' {{IPA-uk|nɑˈtɑlʲɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Natalie (given name)|Natalie]], of Latin origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Ніна}}''' ''([[Nina (name)|Nina]]'' {{IPA-uk|ˈnʲinɑ|}}), from [[Nino (name)|Nino]], of ambiguous ancient [[Near East]]ern origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Оксана}}''' ''([[Oksana]]'' {{IPA-uk|ɔkˈsɑnɑ|}}), '''{{lang|uk|Ксенія}}''' ''(Kseniya'' {{IPA-uk|ˈksɛnʲija|}}), from [[Xenia (name)|Xenia]], of Greek origin. The form ''Oksana'' is most common [[Ukrainians|Ukrainian]] feminine name. * '''{{lang|uk|Олександра}}''' ''(Oleksandra'' {{IPA-uk|ɔlɛkˈsɑndrɑ|}}), '''{{lang|uk|Леся}}''' ''(Lesya'' {{IPA-uk|ˈlɛsʲɑ|}}), '''{{lang|uk|Олеся}}''' ''(Olesya'' {{IPA-uk|ɔˈlɛsʲɑ|}}), feminine of ''Oleksandr,'' equivalent to [[Alexandra]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Олена}}''' ''(Olena'' {{IPA-uk|ɔˈlɛnɑ|}}), from [[Helena (given name)|Helena]], equivalent to [[Elaine (given name)|Elaine]], [[Ellen]] and [[Helen (given name)|Helen]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Ольга}}''' ''(Ol'ha'' {{IPA-uk|ˈɔlʲɦɑ|}}), feminine of ''Oleh,'' a pre-Christian name derived from [[Helga]], of [[Varangian]] origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Парасковія}}''' ''(Paraskoviya'' {{IPA-uk|pɑrɑˈskɔwijɑ|}}), from [[Paraskevi (disambiguation)|Paraskeve]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Пелагея}}''' ''(Pelaheya),'' '''{{lang|uk|Пелагія}}''' ''(Pelahiya'' {{IPA-uk|pɛlɑˈɦijɑ|}}), from [[Pelagia]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Раїса}}''' ''([[Raisa (given name)|Rayisa]]'' {{IPA-uk|rɑˈjisɑ|}}). * '''{{lang|uk|Романа}}''' ''(Romana),'' feminine of ''Roman.'' * '''{{lang|uk|Руслана}}''' ''(Ruslana'' {{IPA-uk|ruˈslɑnɑ|}}), feminine of ''Ruslan.'' * '''{{lang|uk|Світлана}}''' ''([[Svetlana|Svitlana]]'' {{IPA-uk|sʲwitˈlɑnɑ|}}), means "shining one", of Slavic origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Святослава}}''' ''(Svyatoslava),'' feminine of ''Svyatoslav.'' * '''{{lang|uk|Сніжана}}''' ''(Snizhana'' {{IPA-uk|sʲnʲiˈʒɑnɑ|}}). * '''{{lang|uk|Соломія}}''' ''(Solomiya'' {{IPA-uk|sɔlɔˈmijɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Salome (given name)|Salome]], of Hebrew origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Софія}}''' ''(Sofiya'' {{IPA-uk|sɔˈfijɑ|}}), from [[Sophia (name)|Sophia]], equivalent to [[Sophie]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Стефанія}}''' ''([[Stefania (name)|Stefaniya]]'' {{IPA-uk|stɛˈfɑnʲijɑ|}}), '''{{lang|uk|Степанія}}''' ''(Stepaniya),'' '''{{lang|uk|Степанида}}''' ''(Stepanyda'' {{IPA-uk|stɛpɑˈnɪdɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Stephanie]], masculine of ''Stefan'' and ''Stepan,'' of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Таїсія}}''' ''(Tayisiya'' {{IPA-uk|tɑˈjisʲijɑ|}}), '''{{lang|uk|Таїса}}''' ''(Tayisa'' {{IPA-uk|tɑˈjisɑ|}}), from [[Thaïs]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Тамара}}''' ''([[Tamara (given name)|Tamara]]),'' from [[Tamar (name)|Tamar]], of Hebrew origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Текля}}''' ''(Teklya'' {{IPA-uk|ˈtɛklʲɑ|}}), from [[Thecla]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Тетяна}}''' ''([[Tatyana|Tetyana]]'' {{IPA-uk|tɛˈtʲɑnɑ|}}), of Latin origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Уляна}}''' ''(Ulyana'' {{IPA-uk|uˈlʲɑnɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Gillian]] or [[Juliana (disambiguation)|Juliana]], of Latin origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Федора}}''' ''(Fedora'' {{IPA-uk|fɛˈdɔrɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Theodora (given name)|Theodora]], masculine of ''Fedir,'' ''Fedor,'' ''Khvedir'' and ''Teodor,'' of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Христина}}''' ''([[Christina (given name)|Khrystyna]]'' {{IPA-uk|xrɪˈstɪnɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Christine (name)|Christine]], of Greek origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Юлія}}''' ''(Yuliya'' {{IPA-uk|ˈjulʲijɑ|}}), equivalent to [[Julia]] and [[Julie (given name)|Julie]], of Latin origin. * '''{{lang|uk|Яніна}}''' ''([[Yanina (disambiguation)|Yanina]]),'' diminutive of ''Yana,'' equivalent to [[Janine (given name)|Janine]]. * '''{{lang|uk|Ярослава}}''' ''(Yaroslava'' {{IPA-uk|jɑrɔˈslɑwɑ|}}), feminine of ''Yaroslav.''
{{col-end}}
Other popular given names include: Levko, etc.
